===Etymology===
From [[Serbo-Croatian]] '''rakija''' < possibly from [[Arabic]] {{ARchar|[[عرق]]}} ('araq) meaning [[sweat]] or [[wine]] (as the rakija or wine vapor drops are similar to drops of sweat). Exact etymology is hard to pinpoint as this word (or a variant of it) is found throughout the Balkans, the Mediterranean and the Middle East.
